What is overall transaction distribution and difference
Since each category has a different value range, applying scale of log10 to make the ranges comparable in the same graph. Education expense has the lowest average value, while shelter expense has the highest. Recreation expense exhibits a larger variance, whereas food expense is more centered.


Show the code
p <- df_average %>%
  tidyr::pivot_longer(cols = c(Education,Food,Recreation,Shelter,Wage), names_to = "Category", values_to = "Value") %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = Value, fill = Category)) +
  geom_density_interactive(aes(tooltip=Category),alpha=0.8) +
  #generate a discrete version from "viridis" color palette
  scale_fill_viridis_d(option = "D")+
  scale_y_continuous(NULL,           
                     breaks = NULL)+
  ggtitle("Financial transaction distribution")+
  scale_x_log10()


tooltip_css <- "
  .girafe-tooltip {
    background-color: #FFFFFF;
    border: 1px solid #AAAAAA;
    padding: 5px;
    border-radius: 5px;
  }

  .girafe-tooltip span {
    color: inherit !important;
  }
"

# Create the girafe object with options
girafe(
  ggobj = p,
  width_svg = 6,
  height_svg = 6 * 0.618,
  options = list(
    opts_tooltip(
      css = tooltip_css
    )
  )
)
